description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Associate Specialist / Specialty Doctor&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Birmingham&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Packages up to £80K depending on experience (plus generous on-call payments)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;St Andrew’s Healthcare is a charity with an excellent and well-deserved reputation as a provider of specialist mental healthcare. We transform the lives of people with the greatest mental health needs. Throughout our 180 year history we have helped some of society’s most vulnerable people and today we proudly continue to build world-class mental healthcare services. Our commitment to holistic care, safety, recovery and innovative therapies and treatment makes St Andrew’s the perfect place to take your career to a new level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;St Andrew’s Birmingham is a 124 bedded adult mental healthcare facility, located in Stirchley and comprises of eight units which cover medium and low security. At present, 6 of the wards provide services for Men and two is for women.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Birmingham sevice also offers an excellent opportunity to deliver value-based healthcare focusing on clinical outcomes. The Birmingham site is part of the West Midlands Provider collaborative which offers great opportunities to work alongside NHS colleagues to deliver the best possible care for patients in the region.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;About the role&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an opportunity for non-consultant grade Doctors to help shape our essential services. Joining an experienced and supportive team, you will demonstrate strong clinical skills within your professional field.The role will primarily involve providing essential day to day holistic healthcare to a defined cohort of in-patients as part of a comprehensive multi-disciplinary team, in conjunction with a supervising responsible/approved clinician.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MRCPsych or equivalent is desirable (but not essential) and membership of the GMC will be required. Further career progression in terms of Section 12(2) approval, Approved Clinician status, will be encouraged and supported.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Why Choose St Andrew’s?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Competitive salary&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Separately remunerated on call duties available&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A tailored comprehensive induction programme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Medical indemnity cover&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Supportive working environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Huge opportunities for Continuing Professional Development with regular onsite educational &amp; training events and a dedicated research department&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support for appraisal and revalidation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Autonomy to make decisions to improve patient outcomes&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Opportunities for involvement in regional provider collaborative.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Relocation allowance available (subject to status)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
